  "exec_summary": "The European Banking Authority has introduced guidelines for ESG banking products, while the European Securities and Markets Authority has been actively enforcing regulations, warning Polymarket that its prediction markets may violate EU rules and registering Standard Chartered under the MiCA license, which has become a key requirement for crypto firms in Europe as of the July 1 MiCA deadline. In a related development, Revolut will delist USDT in Europe due to Tether's lack of a MiCA license. Meanwhile, in a Belgium-related development, although not directly mentioned, the broader EU regulatory environment will likely impact Belgian financial institutions, particularly with regards to ESG and crypto regulations.",
